<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The initialization int32 return_code = OS_ERROR; is dead code. The variable is either returned directly via an early return (OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_STATE) before use, or is always assigned inside the while(true) loop (set to OS_SUCCESS, OS_ERR_INVALID_ID, or OS_ERR_OBJECT_IN_USE) before being inspected/used after the loop. Removing the initial assignment to OS_ERROR would not change program behaviour, so this executed assignment violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
